"One of my go-to activities, when I'm getting uninspired, is to read. I find that my mind wanders quite nicely, so I'm able to come up with some exciting ideas. Of course. latestIgtvVideos.caption:
“IamTeejh” is all about celebrating & talking about Indian women who are following their passions and pushing through adversities to achieve their goals. This month we unfold another inspiring chapter with Sanjana Goenka @lineandcoconut who is an artist, graphic designer, and content writer.

We asked her about what led her to pursue art and this is what she had to say -

"I sort of grew up around art, my parents always being quite into it. We had a lot of art at home and it's always sort of been a big part of my life from a visual perspective. I've also always just enjoyed drawing and painting. I started when I was three years old, and, yeah, I never stopped. I think what finally nudged me to pursue it as a full-time career was my mental health. If I'm being completely honest, it definitely helped keep my mind at peace."

Durga Pujo is one of the most anticipated festivals in West Bengal and other eastern states like Assam, Tripura, Odisha and Jharkhand. Throughout the nine days, Pujo fever grips everyone, regardless of age, caste, class, or gender.✨

With its beautiful and melodious conch sound, dhol beats, mantra chants and elaborately designed pandals with life size statues of Goddess Durga , the entire state of West Bengal celebrates Durga Pujo with open arms and hearts filled with incomprehensible feelings of togetherness.Dressed in traditional attire, devotees offer prayers in the evening and perform a dhunuchi naach, a special dance with earthen lamps.The colourful cultural displays, the lively atmosphere, the bright lights adorning the city-under the spell of Durga Puja, the City of Joy surely does begin to do justice to its name. Dancing to upbeat dhaak beats, going on a pandal-hopping spree, munching on lip-smacking bhogs, wearing beautiful attire is a must-do during Durga puja in West Bengal.✨

In conversation with @sway_instyle on what inspired her to be a part of the fashion industry.

"What inspired me to be in the fashion world, honestly, I think my inspiration comes from my mother. She’s been somebody who loves fabric, stitching, designing. I think it is in her blood. Growing up, my mother and I would go shopping for fabrics every week and we were kind of crazy about it, we would bond over it, we would design fabrics. We would just get up and be like “There’s an exhibition in town! Do you want to go? Do you want to check the fabrics out! And that would really excite us! I think, I didn't realize that I had an inclination in that space till I quit and had some clarity."
